quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  91,1,(I swear) by the sun and its radiant light
  91,2,And the moon that trails (and reflects) its light
  91,3,By the day that reveals (the sun)
  91,4,And the night that veils it
  91,5,"(I swear) by the sky, and (by) Him Who made it"
  91,6,"And (by) the earth, and (by) Him Who spread it"
  91,7,"By the soul, and by Him Who perfected it"
  91,8,"Then, inspired in it the (conscience, the sense of) wrong and right"
  91,9,"Successful is the one, who (nurtured and) purified (his soul)"
  91,10,A (dismal) failure is the one who (suppressed and) debased (his soul)
  91,11,The (people of) ´Samood´ denied (the truth) with utter arrogance
  91,12,The meanest among them was dispatched
  91,13,"(Against) the messenger of Allah (who) warned them saying, \"(Do not attack) this camel of Allah; let it (roam and) drink (freely)"
  91,14,"But they refused, and slashed its hamstring. Therefore, as a consequence of their sins, their Lord destroyed them completely; He totally demolished their dwellings"
  91,15,For He does not fear (any) consequence